helptext.en:
Fossil Common Names - To add

Common Name Uncertain - To add

Scientific Name - Assign formal higher taxonomic name, especially if specimen is not identifiable to Genus and species name (e.g., Actinopterygii).

Open Nomenclature Term - To add

Other Scientific Name - To add

Fossil Identification Uncertain - To add

Fossil Size Category - To add

Additional Taxonomic Information - Note any alternate scientific names (e.g., if taxon name changed over time such as Alnus crispoides = Alnus hollandiana) or informal taxonomic designation of a name (e.g., actinopterygian). Do not repeat common names here.

Fossil Part - Select the type of fossil part  (tooth, bone, fish scale, shell, leaf, needle).

Other Fossil Part or Fossil Part Details - To add

Trace Fossil - Select the type of trace fossil (burrow, track, gastrolith, coprolite, etc).

Other Trace Fossil or Trace Fossil Details - To add

Fossil Condition - Select if specimen is complete, fragment or unidentifiable.

Fossil Preservation - Select the preservation (original material, mineralization, mold, cast, imprint, compression, carbonized impression, recrystallization).

Fossil Notes - To add (maximum 80 characters)
